<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_647 bio.xml#_648">The Roulins</rs> owned <hi rend="italics">Augustine Roulin (‘La berceuse’) </hi>(<rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_2773">F 505 / JH 1669</rs>). It cannot be ascertained which portrait of Joseph Roulin was in their possession; <ref target="let774.xml#n-3">see letter 774, n. 3.</ref> In 1900 Vollard bought eight Van Goghs from Roulin (Paris, Musée d’Orsay, Documentation, Archives Vollard): five portraits (<ref target="let796.xml#n-3">see letter 796, n. 3</ref>), two landscapes (<ref target="let836.xml">see letter 836</ref>) and a still life with oleanders (<rs type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#noill_746">F 594 / JH 1567</rs>). See Priou 1955, p. 27.</p>
